Design Decisions:
    First and foremost, the main thing I did was not use the Edge and Vertex classes that were provided. I found it to
    be easier to put everything into a 2D array (my adjacency matrix), and do all my computation from there.
    I did not make a structure for the adjacency matrix, however I did consider it. I just thought it would be easier
    to tranverse a 2D array rather than a series of structs. To compute the path for Djikstra's, I used 2 arrays, one that
    keeps all the nodes that I have visited, and another that tracks the current distance I have traveled to find a certain node.
    We initialized all the nodes with some large arbitrary value so that we know that we haven't currently found a path. Then we scan through the whole scoreboard and pick the node with the smallest distance. Once we find the shortest path, we mark it as visited, and use that as a "stepping stone". This keeps running until we find the shortest distance from the node we are concerned with and then we move onto the next node. This keeps running until we find the shortest distance possible.